stateDiagram-v2
    direction LR

    [*] --> Idle
    Idle --> Initializing : init()

    state Initializing {
        direction TB
        [*] --> CheckingDependencies
        CheckingDependencies --> ConnectingToServices : Dependencies OK
        ConnectingToServices --> [*] : Services Connected
    }
    note right of Initializing
        The init() method is asynchronous.
        It performs setup tasks like dependency checks and service connections.
    end note

    Initializing --> Ready : onInitSuccess
    Initializing --> Error : onInitFailure

    Ready --> Processing : startOperation()
    Processing --> Ready : onOperationComplete
    Processing --> Ready : onOperationFailure
    note left of Processing
        Operation failures do not terminate the manager.
        The system returns to a 'Ready' state to accept new operations.
        Errors should be logged and handled appropriately.
    end note

    Ready --> Destroying : destroy()
    Error --> Destroying : destroy()
    Error --> Initializing : retryInit()

    Destroying --> [*] : onDestroyComplete